name: Kebab
instructions:
1)Mix almond flour and paking powder in bread size recipient
2)Add oil and egg
3)Beat it like you are making an omelette
4)Microwave on high for 90 seconds

Note: I usually cut the bread and fill it with cheese and turkey and put it on a frying pan
additionalInfo: These kebabs are so good! I first made them to go camping. My were going to barbeque but I wanted something different than just meat and burguers. So, I did the kebabs a few days before and kept them on the freezer.
